ííŸ@b9842b7bb216775af5c80220013d55b6a663d1571007b7d211ef544bf04aa3a5⁄™Title: Filters
Path: Filters
Content:
A primary goal of Nushell is the ability to easily handle structured data in the pipeline. Nushell contains an extensive set of commands known as "filters" designed to meet these needs.
A sample of filter commands is listed in this Guide below. For the current list of commands categorized as filters, you can run:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
help commands | where category == filters

```
íŸ@5cf1750b6602dd4cd43666c3189f559b8e096845d10519bc831c5aa8697f6417⁄ñTitle: Filters
Path: Filters vs. Flow Control Statements
Content:
While it's certainly possible to modify structured data using "traditional" flow control statements like 
``for``
 or 
``while``
, filters are usually more convenient and (often far) more performant. See the 
[link: /book/variables.html#choosing-between-mutable-and-immutable-variables] Variables section of The Book
 for more information.
